esqlQuery.esql:
// Alert when no API server metrics are received — server may be down.
//
// What triggers this alert:
// Zero documents received from the API server data stream within the time window.
//
// What it means:
// Complete control plane failure or monitoring pipeline issue.
//
// Common causes:
// API server crash, network partition, monitoring agent failure, cluster-wide outage.
//
// Action needed:
// Immediately check cluster health, API server status, and network connectivity.
//
// To scope to a cluster, add: AND `orchestrator.cluster.name` == "YOUR_CLUSTER"
TS metrics-kubernetes.apiserver-*
| STATS doc_count = COUNT(*) BY `orchestrator.cluster.name`
| WHERE doc_count < 1
